						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the central shrine in the Naṭanapādēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kulōttuṅga I. Year 48: 1117-18 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of 96 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp to god Tirukkaṇṇīśvaram-uḍaiyār in Śōḻakulavallinallūr in Paṭṭāṉpākkai-nāḍu in Gaṅgaikoṇḍaśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu by Ayi••• ḍaiyāṇ Vīdiviḍaṅgaṉ Tirukkaṇṇīśvaram-uḍaiyāṉ.</p>						

						</summary>
